            "heading": "",
            "text": "<h2>Movement Is a Statement</h2><p>Every time you move in organza, it makes a sound — a soft, crisp rustle that turns heads. It doesn’t trail behind you. It follows you like a shadow with sharp edges. When you walk, the pallu doesn’t flutter – it slices through the air.</p><p>Try dancing in organza, and you’ll realize this fabric doesn’t flow with your body — it creates <strong>geometry</strong>. It flares at angles, stiffens at curves, and makes you <strong>visible</strong>. This is not a saree that lets you disappear in a crowd. It wants you front and center, unapologetic and in control.</p>",
